        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Viscous coupling Inspection"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "619_3.0_jpn_11581942_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Check the viscous coupling (A) for cracks, damage, or oil leakage."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "619_3.0_jpn_11581943_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Mark (B) the propeller shaft (A). Either No. 1 or No. 2 is acceptable. Start the engine and allow it to warm up until the radiator fan operates twice. With the car idling, move the select lever to the L or S position. Parking brake Press the pedal hard and measure the time per 10 revolutions of the propeller shaft.",
      "refs": [
        {
          "id": "R000620",
          "label": "Inspect rear differential fluid.",
          "resolved": true
        },
        {
          "id": "R000625",
          "label": "Replace viscous coupling.",
          "resolved": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "ordered": false,
      "items": [
        {
          "text": "If the time per 10 revolutions is more than 18 seconds, the viscous coupling is normal."
        },
        {
          "text": "If the time per 10 revolutions is more than 18 seconds, the viscous coupling is normal."
        },
        {
          "text": "If the time per 10 revolutions is less than 18 seconds, the viscous coupling or rear differential may be faulty. Inspect rear differential fluid. If it is normal Replace viscous coupling.",
          "refs": [
            {
              "id": "R000620",
              "label": "Inspect rear differential fluid.",
              "resolved": true
            },
            {
              "id": "R000625",
              "label": "Replace viscous coupling.",
              "resolved": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "If the time per 10 revolutions is less than 18 seconds, the viscous coupling or rear differential may be faulty. Inspect rear differential fluid. If it is normal Replace viscous coupling.",
          "refs": [
            {
              "id": "R000620",
              "label": "Inspect rear differential fluid.",
              "resolved": true
            },
            {
              "id": "R000625",
              "label": "Replace viscous coupling.",
              "resolved": true
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "If the parking brake pedal is not returned after measurement, the temperature of the viscous coupling will rise, resulting in deterioration and possible failure."
      ]
    }
  ],
